page.title: 01Rural Landscape
page.content: Our block of squares is a rural one.There are houses of historic interest.There are small communities together with a hamlet. The hamlet of{ {Sewards End}has the remains of a Roman road and a dismantled railway (closed in 1963).There is a long stretch of woodland in the north-west corner of our rectangle. There are many farms in the area.Most of the farmland is arable, but there is some sheep farming.There are no motorways or busy industrial areas but there are two public services, a sub Post Office and a Public House.
